			  	Main Entry: sor·tie <br />
Pronunciation: 'sor-tE, sor-'tE<br />
Function: noun<br />
Etymology: French, from Middle French, from sortir to escape<br />
1 : a sudden issuing of troops from a defensive position against the enemy<br />
2 : one mission or attack by a single plane<br />
3 : FORAY, RAID<br />
